  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nCurrently hard-coded here for xml and html: https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/2.5.0.Final/independent-projects/qute/core/src/main/java/io/quarkus/qute/HtmlEscaper.java#L42\r\n\r\nWhen you have e.g. xhml, you'll probably configure something like:\r\n```\r\nquarkus:\r\n  qute:\r\n    suffixes:\r\n      - xhtml\r\n    content-types:\r\n      xhtml: application/xhtml+xml\r\n```\r\nbut you'd still want escaping for those xhtml templates, which doesn't work, even not with a selected variant (at least for `@CheckedTemplates`; see #21730).\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\n```\r\nquarkus:\r\n  qute:\r\n    html-escape-content-types:\r\n      - xhtml\r\n```\r\n(or a better name)\r\n\r\nMaybe it's better to create a new `content-types` config object that takes:\r\n- file ending\r\n- content-type\r\n- locale (optional)\r\n- encoding (optional)\r\n- escaping yes/no (optional)\r\n\r\nOtherwise the config would become really verbose and not so DRY, IMHO.\r\n\r\nAlso, I think `Variant` should be extended to toggle escaping.\r\n\r\nRelated:\r\n- #21730\r\n- #21405\r\n- https://quarkusio.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/187030-users/topic/Qute.20and.20XML.20templates.20.28char.20escaping.20issues.29",
